  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bossaso Port And Roads Infrastructure Upgrading Puntland State Of Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During the past years, the
situation in the Somali regions called mostly for recurrent humanitarian and
early recovery interventions, generally addressing the same problems over and
over again. With the ongoing trend of stabilization, there is an important
opportunity for sustainable development, if strategic investments in to basic
infrastructure and services are made. Such investments are also crucial to
strengthen the path of peace-building and economic recovery in places that
enjoy relative stability. 



The identification of the
present project&apos;s components is the result of a long consultative and
participatory planning process between UN-Habitat/Somalia and the Puntland
authorities, both central and local. The rehabilitation of the Bossaso port and
urban road system is widely supported and recognized as key priority for the
city and the region (see attached letters of endorsement from various Puntland
authorities).</narrative>
  </description>
